!! Blessing of Abraham

The emphasis of this reading is to highlight the interaction between Abraham and God. We have the following from Genesis 12:1-3

<<<
Now the LORD said to Abram, "Go from your country and your kindred and your father's house to the land that I will show you. And I will make of you a great nation, and I will bless you and make your name great, so that you will be a blessing. I will bless those who bless you, and him who dishonors you I will curse, and in you all the families of the earth shall be bless."
<<<
''Genesis 12:1-3''

We see three particular section of the promises which also connects to how Abraham witnesses it in his own life:

* The Promise of Land
** "to the land that I will show you."
*** God leads Abraham to the Land (Genesis 13:14-15)
* The Promise of Posterity
** "a great nation"
*** Name change (Genesis 17:5)
* The Promise of Blessing
** "I will bless you"
*** Circumcision (Genesis 17:7-8)

!! Immediate Historical Fulfillment
!!! Posterity
Posterity was confirmed through out Abraham's lineage: Isaac (Gen 26:4) and Jacob (Gen 32:12).

Three particular mentions (not exhaustive) of posterity were mentioned after Abraham that indicate that God's promise still stood the test of time:

* Egyptian Slavery

<<<
But the people of Israel were fruitful and increased greatly; they multiplied and grew exceedingly strong, so that the land was filled with them.
<<<
''Exodus 1:7''

which is confirmed in Acts 7:17

<<<
But as the time of the promise drew near, which God had granted to Abraham, the people increased and multiplied in Egypt
<<<
''Acts 7:17''

* King Solomon

<<<
And your servant is in the midst of your people whom you have chosen, a great people, too many to be numbered or counted for multitude.
<<<
''1 Kings 3:8''

* Promise of Restoration

Fast forward 350 some years after Solomon, we see Jeremiah's prophetic promise

<<<
As the host of heaven cannot be numbered and the sands of the sea cannot be measured, so I will multiply the offspring of David my servant, and the Levitical priests who minister to me.”
<<<
''Jeremiah 33:22''

!! Land

The Israelites reached the promise land: Exodus 2:24; 3:6l 32:13. Then again restored after Babylon captivity. But this was not a full promise fulfillment because of Hebrews 11:8-16, 39, 40.

