<<<
Perspectives Pg 6

The apostles quote this in 1 Peter 2:9-10 and Romans 9:24-26.

<<<
This New Testament perspective is essential as we read the Old Testament prophecies, for what we miss in the Old Testament is any clear explanation of just how God's promised blessing would overflow from Abraham and his descendants to "all families o the earth." Although Israel is described as "a light to lighten the nations" and has a mission to "bring forth justice to the nations" (Isaiah 42:1-6; 49:6), we do not actually see this happening. It is only in the Lord Jesus himself that these prophecies are fulfilled, for only in his day are the nations actually included in the redeemed community.
<<<
